   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>On Sun, 7 Aug 2011, aldeka wrote:

&gt; 1.) The projects-with-bugs / projects-without-bugs distinction is 
&gt; unuseful. Heck, the header that separates the two sections is too small 
&gt; to even see! Instead, by default let's only show projects that either 
&gt; have bugs in our system, or have a filled-in project page.

This makes *oodles* of sense!

&gt; 2.) Instead of making people hit enter when they start typing in the 
&gt; /+projects/ search bar, we should auto-filter the projects that appear 
&gt; below based on what they've typed ('aud' -&gt; only projects with 'aud' in 
&gt; the name). That doesn't help with the page being gigantic, long, and 
&gt; barely informative, but at least it makes it faster for someone to get 
&gt; to their desired project page.

Mmm, nice. I like this plan a lot also!</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg2272">msg2272 (view)</a></th>
