  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>1.) The projects-with-bugs / projects-without-bugs distinction is unuseful. Heck, 
the header that separates the two sections is too small to even see! Instead, by 
default let's only show projects that either have bugs in our system, or have a 
filled-in project page. 

2.) Instead of making people hit enter when they start typing in the /+projects/ 
search bar, we should auto-filter the projects that appear below based on what 
they've typed ('aud' -&gt; only projects with 'aud' in the name). That doesn't help 
with the page being gigantic, long, and barely informative, but at least it makes 
it faster for someone to get to their desired project page.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
